oscmux
============

This program redirects Open Sound Control messages comming from an arbitrary number of local ports to an arbitrary number of host ports with arbitrary delays.

command line usage
------------------

redirect messages from local port 3333 to local ports 4444 and 5555
	oscmux -i 3333 -o 4444 -o localhost:5555

multiplex messages from local ports 1111 and 2222 and send them to port 4444 on 10.0.0.1 with a delay of 0.5 seconds
	oscmux -i 1111 -i 2222 -d 0.5 -o 10.0.0.1:4444

redirect messages from local port 2222 to local port 3333 with a delay of 10.1 seconds and to port 4444 on 10.0.0.2 with a delay of 4.3 seconds
	oscmux -i 2222 -d 1.1 3333 -d 4.3 -o 10.0.0.2:4444

multiplex messages from local ports 1111, 2222 and 3333 and send them to local ports 4444, 5555 and 6666
	oscmux -i 1111 -i 2222 -i 3333 -o 4444 -o 5555 -o 6666

